{
  "info": {
    "name": "Monitor PTAP API",
    "description": "Colección de la API real de @ptap/api (actualizada 2026-07-16). Contrato completo: docs/api/openapi.yaml.\n\nCÓMO USARLA\n1. Levanta el backend COMPLETO: `npm run dev:api` (requiere MySQL). El arranque de telemetría (`start:telemetry`) NO tiene auth ni /api/auth/login.\n2. Ejecuta primero **Auth → Login**: guarda el JWT en la variable {{token}} automáticamente; el resto de requests lo usan.\n3. Usuarios de prueba (`npm run db:seed-users -w @ptap/api`), contraseña `Demo1234!`:\n   civil@ptap.co · operador@ptap.co · jefe@ptap.co · admin@ptap.co\n\nAUTORIZACIÓN: por permisos granulares. Sin token → 401; sin el permiso → 403.\nPruébalo: haz login como `civil` y ejecuta *Usuarios → Listar* (403) u *OPC → Info* (403); repite como `admin` (200).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "plantId", "value": "montebello", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "userId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (guarda el token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const ok = pm.response.code === 201 || pm.response.code === 200;",
                  "pm.test('login OK', () => pm.expect(ok).to.be.true);",
                  "if (ok) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.token);",
                  "  console.log('Sesión iniciada como', body.user.email, '| rol:', body.user.role);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@ptap.co\",\n  \"password\": \"Demo1234!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "login"] },
            "description": "Devuelve { token, user }. El rol sale de MySQL, no del email."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Registro (crea SIEMPRE rol civil)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Persona Nueva\",\n  \"email\": \"nuevo@ptap.co\",\n  \"phone\": \"3001112233\",\n  \"plant\": \"montebello\",\n  \"password\": \"Secreta123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "register"] },
            "description": "La cuenta nace SIEMPRE con rol 'civil'. Email duplicado → 409."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Registro con role=admin (DEBE dar 400)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('el servidor rechaza el rol enviado por el cliente (400)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Atacante\",\n  \"email\": \"escalada@ptap.co\",\n  \"plant\": \"montebello\",\n  \"password\": \"Secreta123!\",\n  \"role\": \"admin\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "register"] },
            "description": "Prueba de seguridad: el schema es .strict(), así que enviar 'role' se RECHAZA con 400 en vez de ignorarse. Nadie puede auto-asignarse un rol."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Usuarios (solo Admin)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Listar usuarios",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "users"] },
            "description": "Requiere el permiso manage_users (solo admin). Con token de civil/operador/jefe → 403."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Asignar rol",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"role\": \"operador\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/{{userId}}/role",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "{{userId}}", "role"]
            },
            "description": "Requiere assign_roles (solo admin). Se audita (quién, a quién, de→a). Un admin no puede cambiar su propio rol (400). El rol nuevo aplica cuando el usuario vuelve a iniciar sesión (viaja en el JWT)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Activar / desactivar cuenta",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"isActive\": false\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/users/{{userId}}/active",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "users", "{{userId}}", "active"]
            },
            "description": "Requiere manage_users. Un usuario inactivo no puede iniciar sesión. Un admin no puede desactivarse a sí mismo (400)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Plantas (telemetría)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Listar plantas",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/plants", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "plants"] },
            "description": "Solo exige JWT válido (cualquier rol)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Snapshot de una planta",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/plants/{{plantId}}/snapshot",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "plants", "{{plantId}}", "snapshot"]
            },
            "description": "Desde cache RAM (<50 ms); nunca toca el PLC bajo demanda."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Comandos (Fase 5)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Ejecutar comando",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"command\": \"openValve\",\n  \"target\": \"valveEV01\",\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"demo-001\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/plants/{{plantId}}/commands",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "plants", "{{plantId}}", "commands"]
            },
            "description": "HOY responde 404 TARGET_NOT_WRITABLE: el mapping de producción no tiene señales writable (falta el L5X) y OPCUA_WRITES_ENABLED=false por defecto. El mecanismo está construido y probado; la escritura real sigue cerrada a propósito.\n\nCódigos: 200 confirmado · 502 fallido (sin read-back) · 403 permiso o sesión insegura · 409 interlock."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "OPC (observabilidad)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Status del puente",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/opc/status", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "opc", "status"] },
            "description": "Solo exige JWT válido."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Info del servidor OPC UA (admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/opc/info", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "opc", "info"] },
            "description": "Requiere system_config (solo admin). Con token de civil → 403."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Salud por buffer (admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/opc/buffers", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "opc", "buffers"] },
            "description": "Requiere system_config (solo admin)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Dead letter (admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/opc/dead-letter", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "opc", "dead-letter"] },
            "description": "Requiere system_config (solo admin). Señales anómalas descartadas (regla 12)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Health / Métricas",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health de la app",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "health"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Health de MySQL",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health/db", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "health", "db"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Health industrial del puente",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health/opc", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "health", "opc"] },
            "description": "Público a propósito (liveness/readiness para orquestadores). Devuelve 503 si el bridge está Stale o Faulted."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Métricas Prometheus",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/metrics", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["metrics"] },
            "description": "FUERA del prefijo /api (convención de Prometheus). Abierto salvo que definas METRICS_AUTH_TOKEN."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Socket.IO (referencia — no ejecutable en Postman v2.1)",
      "item": [],
      "description": "El cliente emite `opc:subscribe` { plantId } y recibe:\n- `opc:snapshot` (por planta, SOLO cuando el snapshot cambia)\n- `opc:liveness` (broadcast, en cambios de frescura)\n\n`sequence` es monótono por planta: si llega N+2 sin ver N+1, hubo un hueco → resincronizar por REST.\n\nGap conocido: el gateway NO autentica el handshake (docs/SECURITY_FINDING_P0.md §6)."
    }
  ]
}
